$ Oracle privileges

In order for a user or → development/databases/Oracle/security/roles[role] to access an
→ development/databases/Oracle/objects[object], they need to have the respective privilege. Thus, privileges play an important role
for → development/databases/Oracle/security[security].

Privilages can be given and taken away with the → development/databases/Oracle/SQL/DCL[DCL] statements
→ development/databases/Oracle/SQL/DCL/grant[`grant`] and
→ development/databases/Oracle/SQL/DCL/revoke[`revoke`].

Which user has which privileges can be queried in the → development/databases/Oracle/installed/data-dictionary[data dictionary] views
  • → development/databases/Oracle/installed/data-dictionary/role/privs[dba_role_privs]
  • → development/databases/Oracle/installed/data-dictionary/tab/privs[dba_tab_privs]
  • → development/databases/Oracle/installed/data-dictionary/sys_privs[dba_sys_privs]
  • → development/databases/Oracle/installed/data-dictionary/role/role_privs[role_role_privs]
  • → development/databases/Oracle/installed/data-dictionary/role/sys_privs[role_sys_privs]
  • → development/databases/Oracle/installed/data-dictionary/role/tab_privs[role_tab_privs]

sa:

  → development/databases/Oracle/installed/data-dictionary/connect_role_grantees/index
